      "job_description": "About This Role\n\nWe are seeking a highly skilled Windows Application Experience Developer to build and evolve the core application. This is a hands-on role focused on designing, developing, and maintaining high-performance Windows applications across both modern and legacy operating systems. You will be responsible for bringing complex features to life through elegant implementation and thoughtful attention to design, performance, and usability.\n\nOur ideal candidate has a deep understanding of Windows architecture and APIs, with experience building visually polished applications that run reliably across different environments. You know how to transform ambitious UI concepts into clean, scalable code. You are comfortable navigating technical constraints, debugging issues across OS versions, and continuously sharpening your skills with new tools and languages.\n\nYou will collaborate closely with designers, engineers, and strategists to define features, solve problems, and deliver exceptional experiences for users and organizations. You will participate in code reviews, contribute to architectural decisions, and take full ownership of your work from planning through deployment. We operate at a fast pace, value initiative, and look for developers who balance strong technical execution with a clear understanding of user needs and business goals. If this is the kind of environment where you do your best work, we'd like to meet you.\n\nKey Responsibilities\n• Design, develop, and maintain high-performance Windows applications for both modern and older versions of the Windows operating system.\n• Bring development forward with new features and the implementations of designs that bring the app to life, delighting users and organizations alike.\n• Collaborate with cross-functional teams to define, design, and implement new features.\n• Ensure applications are optimized for performance, security, and usability.\n• Debug and resolve complex technical issues across different versions of Windows.\n• Stay informed about the latest Windows development tools, trends, and technologies.\n• Participate in code reviews, ensuring adherence to best practices and high coding standards.\n• Manage multiple projects simultaneously, delivering high-quality solutions on time.\n• Take ownership of projects, making informed decisions to meet client and business needs.\n\nRequired Qualifications\n• Proven experience as a Windows Application Developer with a strong portfolio of completed projects.\n• Proven experience bringing complex visual designs to life in projects that delight users and organizations.\n• Proficiency in languages and technologies such as C++, C#, and .NET.\n• Experience in developing applications for both current and older versions of Windows (e.g., Windows 10, 11, and legacy versions like Windows 7).\n• Strong understanding of Win32, other Windows APIs, system internals, and the Windows SDK.\n• Experience working in a fast-paced agency environment or similar setting.\n• Excellent problem-solving skills and the ability to work independently and collaboratively.\n• Strong communication skills, with the ability to convey complex technical concepts to both technical and non-technical stakeholders.\n\nPreferred Qualifications\n• Experience in transforming UI/UX designs into XAML.\n• Knowledge of network programing and protocols.\n• Knowledge of crypto theory (PKI) and SGX enclave will be a plus.\n• Experience working with the TPM and with the Media Foundation Pipeline.\n• Familiarity with Windows security features and best practices.\n• Familiarity with agile methodologies.",
